- Configure Tauri Android project initialization and signing
- Build and publish APK artifacts to GitHub releases alongside desktop builds
- Consider adding APK signing with keystore for production releases

## DevDash

- I want the integration of runing services and their logs in one app
- I want to create new services and run them in one app
- I want Ngrok integration to expose my local services
- I want to see my system settings and their status in one app
- I want to see my system information and their status in one app
- It should have keyboard shortcuts for all the features and option to customize them
- Each workspace should have random name of random stuff like animals, colors, etc. and option to change it if user wants to. This will make it more fun and less boring to use the app. It will also help user to remember which workspace is for what purpose. For example, if I have a workspace for my personal projects and another workspace for my work projects, I can name them "Blue Whale" and "Red Fox" respectively. This way I can easily identify which workspace is for which purpose without having to read the name every time.
- A settings page where user can customize the app according to their needs and preferences. For example, user can change the theme of the app, the font size, the color scheme, etc. This will make the app more personalized and enjoyable to use. It will also allow user to optimize the app for their workflow and productivity. For example, if I prefer a dark theme and a larger font size, I can easily change that in the settings page without having to use any third-party tools or extensions.
- A dashboard page where user can see all the important information and status of their system and services at a glance. For example, user can see the CPU and memory usage, the network status, the running services and their logs, etc. This will help user to monitor their system and services more efficiently and effectively. It will also allow user to quickly identify any issues or problems that may arise and take appropriate actions to resolve them.
- Text editor for conf files and code snippets with syntax highlighting and auto-completion. This will allow user to edit their configuration files and code snippets directly in the app without having to switch to another text editor or IDE. It will also provide a more seamless and integrated experience for user when working with their services and projects. For example, if I need to edit the configuration file for my web server, I can simply open it in the built-in text editor, make the necessary changes, and save it without having to leave the app or use any external tools.
- Integration with popular code hosting platforms like GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, etc. This will allow user to easily access and manage their repositories and projects directly from the app. It will also provide a more streamlined and efficient workflow for user when working with their code and projects. For example, if I want to clone a repository from GitHub, I can simply enter the repository URL in the app, and it will automatically clone it for me without having to use any command-line tools or external applications.
